55. D. Iam hercle ego illunc nominabo] Plautus here alludes, in all probability, to a privilege accorded by the laws of the XII. Tables to creditors. In virtue of this any one who had a claim against another might, if the legal evidence were defective, proeeed to the house of his debtor and publicly demand payment in loud and abusive language, so as to bring shame upon the defaulter among his neigh- bours.
